HEADWORD: Namaycush
<hw>Nam"ay*cush</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Indian
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large North American lake trout
(<spn>Salvelinus namaycush</spn>). It is usually spotted with red, and
sometimes weighs over forty pounds. Called also <altname>Mackinaw
trout</altname>, <altname>lake trout</altname>, <altname>lake
salmon</altname>, <altname>salmon trout</altname>,
<altname>togue</altname>, and <altname>tuladi</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Namby-pamby</ent>⟦br⟧
